  <section class="spec-sec" id="s10">
    <h2><span class="num">10</span>CLI</h2>
    <p>Three stages, run in order. The extract and transform stages are shared with ghost2astro. The load stage diverges: it generates a seed script instead of writing Markdown files.</p>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">portage · ghost → payload</span><span class="meta">bash</span></div>
      <pre is:raw"><span class="pr">$</span> npx portage extract <span class="fl">--from</span> ghost <span class="fl">--export</span> ./ghost-export.json <span class="fl">--to</span> ./payload-project
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage transform <span class="fl">--target</span> payload
<span class="pr">$</span> npx portage load <span class="fl">--method</span> seed <span class="fl">--images</span> download</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Values</th><th>Default</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--export</span></td><td><span class="ty">path</span></td><td>—</td><td>Ghost JSON export file (required).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--target</span></td><td><span class="ty">payload</span></td><td><span class="ty">astro</span></td><td>Destination platform. <code>payload</code> triggers seed script generation.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--method</span></td><td><span class="ty">seed · rest</span></td><td><span class="ty">seed</span></td><td>Load method. <code>seed</code> generates <code>src/seed.ts</code>. <code>rest</code> pushes via <code>POST /api/{collection}</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--payload-url</span></td><td><span class="ty">url</span></td><td><span class="ty">http://localhost:3000</span></td><td>Payload REST API base URL (rest method only).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--ghost-url</span></td><td><span class="ty">url</span></td><td>—</td><td>Ghost site URL for resolving <code>__GHOST_URL__</code> placeholders.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--content</span></td><td><span class="ty">lexical · html</span></td><td><span class="ty">lexical</span></td><td>Body content format for Payload.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--images</span></td><td><span class="ty">download · localize-external</span></td><td><span class="ty">download</span></td><td>Download images to <code>media/</code> for Local API upload.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--batch-size</span></td><td><span class="ty">number</span></td><td><span class="ty">50</span></td><td>Documents per batch (rest method).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--batch-delay</span></td><td><span class="ty">ms</span></td><td><span class="ty">100</span></td><td>Delay between batches (rest method).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--include-drafts</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">on</span></td><td>Drafts included by default for payload target.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="gf">--dry-run</span></td><td><span class="ty">flag</span></td><td><span class="ty">off</span></td><td>Plan &amp; diff only; write nothing.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <h3>Seed vs. REST</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th></th><th>Seed script</th><th>REST API push</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Requires running server</strong></td><td>No — runs against SQLite directly</td><td>Yes — Payload must be listening</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>File uploads</strong></td><td>Native via <code>filePath</code></td><td>Multipart <code>FormData</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Access control</strong></td><td>Bypassed (<code>overrideAccess: true</code>)</td><td>Needs API key or admin credentials</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Speed</strong></td><td>Fast — no HTTP overhead</td><td>Slower — per-request HTTP round-trip</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Best for</strong></td><td>Initial migration, local development</td><td>Remote Payload instances, CI/CD</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="spec-sec" id="s11">
    <h2><span class="num">11</span>Verification</h2>
    <p>Verification is different from the Astro routes because the destination is a running CMS, not a file tree. You verify by checking Payload's database and admin panel.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Dry-run first</strong> — <code>--dry-run</code> prints the full plan: how many documents in each collection, which images will be downloaded, which relationships will be wired. Nothing is written.</li>
      <li><strong>Manifest ledger</strong> — <code>portage.manifest.json</code> records every source entity, its Ghost ID, the Payload collection it targets, and the transform applied.</li>
      <li><strong>Count reconciliation</strong> — extract counts are compared against <code>payload.find()</code> counts after seeding. Any delta (skipped, failed, HTML-fallback) is listed explicitly.</li>
      <li><strong>Admin spot-check</strong> — open <code>http://localhost:3000/admin</code>, navigate to Posts, verify titles, slugs, tags, authors, and feature images render correctly.</li>
      <li><strong>Relationship integrity</strong> — query a post's <code>tags</code> and <code>authors</code> at <code>depth: 1</code> to confirm relationships resolved correctly.</li>
      <li><strong>Image rendering</strong> — verify feature images display in the admin list view and on the post edit screen. Check <code>/media/</code> serves image files.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar"><span class="name">verification · local api</span><span class="meta">typescript</span></div>
      <pre is:raw"><span class="k">const</span> result = <span class="k">await</span> payload.find({
  collection: <span class="s">'posts'</span>,
  depth: 1,
  pagination: <span class="k">false</span>,
});

console.log(<span class="s">`Posts in Payload: ${result.docs.length}`</span>);
console.log(<span class="s">`Posts with tags: ${result.docs.filter(p => p.tags?.length).length}`</span>);
console.log(<span class="s">`Posts with feature image: ${result.docs.filter(p => p.featureImage).length}`</span>);</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <span class="lbl">Paired template</span>
      <p>The Astro + Payload template from Salish Sea Creatives includes a pre-configured Payload instance (SQLite, collection configs, admin panel) and an Astro frontend that queries Payload's Local API. Spin it up, run the seed script, and verify content in the admin panel. No cloud accounts needed.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
